$ HTML Attribute: itemscope
@ itemscope

`itemscope` defines the scope of associated metadata.

`itemscope` is a boolean attribute.

An → development/web/HTML/tags[HTML element] that uses `itemscope` must also specify either
  • `itemtype` or
  • `itemref`

code {
<div itemscope
     itemtype="→ https://schema.org/Thing[https://schema.org/Thing]" >

     <div class="…" itemprop="name"      >…</div>
     <div class="…" itemprop="identifier">…</div>

</div>
code }
